Archive Corp said it signedan agreement under which &lt;Microamerica>, a value-added resellerof personal computers, peripherals and supplies, willdistribute its Archive XL tape drive.   Archive said Microamerica will carry both models of the XLdrive, a 40-megabyte, 5.25-inch drive based on the QIC-40standard that is compatible with the IBM PC/XT and PC/AT PCs. Reuter&#3;